arriage certificate.General Category BPL Families, General / OBC / SC / ST families (Non-BPL) having land holding less than 2.5 acres and Income less than Rs. 1 lakh p.aRs. 11,000Rs. 10,000 before or on marriage and 1000 within 6 months after marriage on submission of marriage certificate.Sports Woman (any caste or any income)Rs. 31,000For detailed notification on the mukhyamantri vivah shagun yojana amount, please see the link:- http://haryanascbc.gov.in/sites/default/files/documents/indira-gandhi-notifications.pdfMukhyamantri Vivah Shagun Yojana DocumentsCandidates must possess the following documents to avail the benefits of this social welfare scheme:-List of DocumentsAadhaar CardBPL CardPermanent Resident ProofMarriage Invitation CardCaste Certificate (if applicable)Groom\u2019s Board MarksheetsGroom\u2019s Age ProofBride Board MarksheetsBride Age ProofBride\u2019s Account Number, IFSC Code & Branch NameDivorce Order in case of Divorcee womenParent\u2019s Income CertificateHaryana Welfare Scheme EligibilityAll the applicants must fulfill the following eligibility criteria to become eligible to fill mukhyamantri kanya vivah shagun yojana form:- \u2014 Applicant must be a resident of Haryana. \u2014 Minimum age of the bride should be 18 years. \u2014 Minimum age of the groom should be 21 years. \u2014 In a family, mukhyamantri vivah shagun yojana amount can be given upto marriage of 2 daughters of a person. \u2014 Any Widow or divorced women can also take this amount for her re-marriage (only if she had not taken it previously). To see more details on procedure to fill Mukhyamantri Vivah Shagun Yojana 2018, please click the link \u2013 haryanascbc.gov.in  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}